$Id$

---
Intro

(If you installed via yum you can skip to post install section below)

1-.  RPM and yum based install is now available.

yum setup:

Download http://unixservice.com/rpm/i386/unxsyum-1.0-1.i386.rpm

# rpm -i unxsyum-1.0-1.i386.rpm
# yum search unxsvz

rpm's can be used alone and can be found here:

http://unixservice.com/rpm

---
Post Install

1-. Setting up MySQL replication cluster.

2-. Setting up rrdtool datacenter, node and container graphics. Customize the gfx crontab scripts.

3-. Customizing allnodescp.sh.

4-. Installing /vz/template/cache, /etc/vz/conf/ contents. And adding them to tConfig and tOSTemplate.

5-. Configuring unxsVZ via the web interface.

6-. Creating test containers and exercizing them for automonics, live migration etc.

7-. Optionally change /var/www/unxs/html/images/unxslogo.png to your own logo.


---
If you repackage an rpm for FreeBSD, OpenSolaris, OpenBSD etc...please let us know and we will add it to the 
repo above.


